      "She is dedicated to improving the oral health and overall health of her patients: preventing oral disease, and teaching patients about the links between a healthy mouth and a healthy body. She loves being a dentist and serving her patients through conscious, mindful care.",
      "Her commitment reaches past the office. She has served on the Board of Directors for the Washington Dental Service Foundation since 2015, sat on a 2016 Washington State Health Care Authority task force to improve Adult Dental Medicaid benefits, stays active with the ABCD Program (Access to Baby and Child Dentistry), and is Affiliate Faculty for the University of Washington Department of Pediatric Dentistry.",
      "She has two active sons who keep her on her toes. The family enjoys hiking the trails in Snohomish County and biking the Centennial Trail, and she and her husband like golfing and going out for sushi. On her own time, she loves to run and read.",
