      "Kayleen, also a scheduling coordinator, joined the team in 2025 with 8 years of experience building trusting relationships. She comes from a background in personal banking, which gave her excellent organizational skills and a passion for helping people feel taken care of, and she’s often one of the first friendly faces patients meet. A Washington native who grew up in Lake Stevens, she enjoys playing board games with her husband and spending time with their dog, Millie.",
